Hmmm... That&#39;s a pain.

How do you know it&#39;s an infinite loop (as opposed to just a really long
one)? Do you know that a counter which should be decreasing is increasing
instead (or never going down)? Do you see a duplicate element come up in
what should be a unique traversal? Is there something that is exposed
which you can check to determine that the loop really won&#39;t terminate or
something you could expose? There probably isn&#39;t much chance, but
if you could, it might make your life easier.

On Sat, 20 Oct 2001, David Corbin wrote:

&gt; I found a bug, so I want to write a test that exposes that bug.
&gt;
&gt; How does one write a unit test that exposes an infinte loop?  Well, writing
&gt; one that exposes it isn&#39;t hard.  How do you expose it with out the test
&gt; hanging?
&gt;
&gt; The only solution I can see is to use two threads, and set a maximum time
